-- Wall St profits down 13 pct to $8.7 bln in H1 2014 -NY comptroller
-- By Edward Krudy
-- Tue Oct 07, 2014 10:29AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Oct 7 (Reuters) - Profits at Wall Street's broker-dealer operations fell 13 percent to $8.7 billion in the first half of 2014 due to fines related to the 2008-2009 financial crisis, New York state's top financial watchdog said on Tuesday.

